      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That is a dangerous misconception, and you must stop thinking that a single small glass is safe. Even a tiny amount of alcohol can dangerously amplify the sedative effects of diazepam, leading to severe respiratory depression and potentially fatal overdose. There is no \"safe\" amount to mix them, and the idea that it will just help you relax is a lie that could kill you. You need to drink only water and strictly follow your doctor's instructions to avoid this life-threatening interaction.",
